If you don't know how to install python do the following

Right Click on My Computer and hit Properties
On the advanced tab, you'll find environment variables

Click on new under system variables and set variable name to 'PythonPath'
Then give the variable value as C:\PythonXX; where XX is your version of python. Simply give the path of where you installed python.

Now search for the path system variable.
Now add C:\Python27\Scripts\ to the end of the variable value by separating it from the other paths with a semi colon.

Now you can click okay and exit.

To run a python script, open your command prompt where your python file exists and simply type python (name of file).py
And you're ready to go!
